          <msContents>
            <summary>Small manuscript used in private or public recitation and prayer focusing on the praise and worship of the Hindu deity Śiva, presenting one thousand of the god's names, such as Maheśvara, Vāmadeva, Skandaguru, Trilocana, among others. Employs some well-known mantras, such as "om̐ namaḥ śivāya."</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Śivasahasranāman</title>
              <title type="vernacular">शिवसहस्रनामन्</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīśivapurāṇe śivasahasranāmanirūpaṇaṃ nāmasaptatinamodhyāyaḥ // (f. 13v).</colophon>
